<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Testing Radio-Cab Speakers
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Testing Radio-Cab Speakers</title>
        <table id="t0805313" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Radio-Cab Speakers</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="1to7"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="7" spanname="1to7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TESTING RADIO-CAB SPEAKERS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Check fuse F5-B for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With ignition ON, measure voltage to gnd. at F5-B and circuit 12M.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-B 12M to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 12M, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (426). Turn ignition ON and measure voltage from circuit 86 to
                                gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(426) 86 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 86, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (427) and measure voltage from (426) circuit 86 to (427) 86-GA.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(426) 86 to (427) 86-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86-GA or 11-GD to gnd., then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Remove fuse F5-C and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Re-install fuse F5-C and measure voltage to gnd. at F5-C and circuit 14AM.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-C 14AM to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 14AM, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Measure voltage from circuit 88B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(426) 88B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 88B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Was the right front speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to step 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (529), and measure resistance across right front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Across right front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (529) and disconnect connector (426). Measure resistance across
                                circuits 86C and 86D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(426) 86C to 86D.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86C or 86D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Was the left front speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to step 14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (530), and measure resistance across left front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Across left front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (530) and disconnect connector (426). Measure resistance across
                                circuits 86A and 86B.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(426) 86A to 86B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86A or 86B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Was the right rear speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to step 18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (528), and measure resistance across right rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Across left rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (528) and disconnect connector (489). Measure resistance across
                                circuits 86U and 86T.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(489) 86U to 86T.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86U or 86T, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (489) and disconnect sleeper speaker connector (472). At (427)
                                measure resistance across circuits 86W and 86V.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(427) 86W to 86V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86W/86U or 86V/86T, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Was the left rear speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to step 22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (531), and measure resistance across left rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Across left rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (531) and disconnect connector (489). Measure resistance across
                                circuits 86R and 86S.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(489) 86R to 86S.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86R or 86S, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (489) and disconnect sleeper speaker connector (472). At (427)
                                measure resistance across circuits 86N and 86P.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(427) 86N to 86P.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86N/86R or 86P/86S, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Power and speaker circuits check good. Reconnect all circuits.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
